Louis Albanese
President, Managing Partner
Louis is the President, Managing Partner of Catamount Wealth Management. He has over 35 years of investment management experience in the securities industry. Prior to founding Catamount, Mr. Albanese was Senior Vice President and Founder of Constitution Capital Corp. Prior to founding Constitution, Mr. Albanese was a Senior Vice President with Prudential Securities in its Portfolio Management Services Program and a Senior Vice President with Paine Webber. He has a BS degree from Fairfield University. Mr. Albanese is active in the community; supporting many community organizations. He serves on the Finance Committee of the Westport Historical Society, is a Board Member of ECHO, a non-profit located in Bridgeport dedicated to building character, enforcing positive behavior and strengthening life skills of youth, and is a member of the Advisory Board of Fairfield University’s Dolan School of Business. Lou resides in Fairfield with his wife, Linda, and has two sons.






Laurie Stefanowicz
Vice President, Managing Partner, Registered Investment Advisor 
Laurie is a Senior Vice President, Managing Partner of Catamount. Her main responsibility is assisting Mr. Albanese with the management of client portfolios. She works with clients to establish a financial plan that meets their individual needs. Prior to joining Catamount, Mrs. Stefanowicz held various sales and marketing positions within the pharmaceutical and sports business industries. She played professional soccer for the Women’s United Soccer Association. She has a BS degree from Vanderbilt University. Laurie is extremely active in our community, she currently serves on the advisory board of Caroline House, volunteers with many other local non-profits and was recognized as one of Fairfield County’s 40 Under 40. In her spare time, she enjoys running, yoga and interior design. Laurie resides in Fairfield with her husband, Jeff, and their two daughters.






Louis Albanese II
Vice President 
Louis is the Vice President of Catamount Wealth Management. He will be a part of the portfolio management team as well as assist with the client development and relationship management needs of the firm. Louis has spent his career obtaining a well-rounded background in finance. He’s done everything from investment banking to private equity. Prior to Catamount, Louis specialized in technology and energy investments. He was an Investment Principal at Saudi Aramco Energy Ventures where he was responsible for investing in technology companies in the renewable energy, oil and gas, information technology, and water sectors. Before joining SAEV, he held finance and strategy roles at First Solar, one of the world’s largest vertically integrated solar companies. Louis started his career in investment banking at Merrill Lynch where he worked out of New York City and Hong Kong. He graduated from Claremont McKenna College with a B.A. in Financial Economics.






Matt Monroe
Associate Portfolio Manager
Matt is an Associate Portfolio Manager. His main responsibility is to expand our firm’s research and analysis capabilities. Prior to joining Catamount, Mr. Monroe was a publishing research analyst on the Clean Technology team at Roth Capital Partners in New York City, concentrating on the advanced lighting, biofuels and energy storage sectors. Prior to that, Matt worked as an Analyst at Manatuck Hill Partners, making investment decisions across asset classes and industries for institutional clients. He began his career at ThinkEquity Partners, a boutique investment bank, where he was a Vice President of Institutional Equity Sales. Matt has a BS degree from Colorado College and currently resides in New York City. In his spare time, he enjoys basketball, running and fine wines, where he has earned a certification from the Court of Master Sommeliers.






Judy Burke
Director Client Relations 
Judy is the Director of Client Relations at Catamount. She is responsible for managing client relationships, day to day client service requests and operations. She also provides trading and general portfolio management support to the portfolio management team. Prior to joining Catamount, Judy was a Client Service Associate for a private wealth management firm in Fairfield County, where she held a similar role and responsibilities. Judy earned her B.S. Degree in Finance from Marymount College. She resides in Weston, CT with her husband and has three grown children. In her spare time Judy enjoys cooking, reading and spending time with her new puppy.

 



 









 

 

